cc:Work.dc:title: Elvie #056
cc:Work.dc:description:
[Elvie is in a room with a collection of boxes, cables and other parts to make up a VR system. Betty is holding a very long invoice]
Elvie: I've bought a new *virtual reality* system. Maybe it's called that because there's *virtually* no Open Source software for it, so the *reality* is that I'll have to buy proprietary games.
Betty: Or perhaps it's because *reality* will really bite when you notice that buying all this kit has *virtually* bankrupted you!
